targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  date_trunc('$timeRange', timestamp_sensor) AS "time",
  entity_id,
  uncertain,
  user_id,
  x1,
  x2,
  y1,
  y2
FROM
  etlocationuser
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(timestamp_sensor)
  AND user_id IN ($user_id)
GROUP BY
  time,
  entity_id,
  uncertain,
  user_id,
  x1,
  x2,
  y1,
  y2
ORDER BY
  time ASC

SELECT
  date_trunc('$timeRange', timestamp_sensor) as time,
  COUNT(*) AS "metric"
FROM
  etlocationuser
WHERE
  user_id IN ($user_id)
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp_sensor)
GROUP BY
  time
ORDER BY
  time;

    p4Values = field ? (field.values.buffer || field.values) : [];
  }
  if (s.refId === "P5") {
    field = s.fields.find((f) => f.name === "P5");
    p5Values = field ? (field.values.buffer || field.values) : [];
  }
  if (s.refId === "P6") {
    field = s.fields.find((f) => f.name === "P6");
    p6Values = field ? (field.values.buffer || field.values) : [];
  }
});

// Calcula la media de los valores de P1
let p1Average = p1Values.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / p1Values.length;
let p2Average = p2Values.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / p2Values.length;
let p3Average = p3Values.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / p3Values.length;
let p4Average = p4Values.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / p4Values.length;
let p5Average = p5Values.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / p5Values.length;
let p6Average = p6Values.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / p6Values.length;

// Convierte la media a un porcentaje
let p1AveragePercentage = p1Average * 100;
let p2AveragePercentage = p2Average * 100;
let p3AveragePercentage = p3Average * 100;
let p4AveragePercentage = p4Average * 100;
let p5AveragePercentage = p5Average * 100;
let p6AveragePercentage = p6Average * 100;

console.log("p1Average", p1Average);

console.log("p3Average", p3Average);
console.log("p4Average", p4Average);
console.log("p5Average", p5Average);

SELECT
  date_trunc('$timeRange', timestamp_sensor) AS "time",
  uncertain AS "P1",
  x1,
  y1,
  x2,
  y2,
  user_id
FROM
  etlocationuser
WHERE
  user_id IN ($user_id)
  AND $__timeFilter(timestamp_sensor)
  AND (
    x1 BETWEEN 0
    AND 8
  )
  AND (
    y1 BETWEEN 0
    AND 7.5
  )
GROUP BY
  time,
  uncertain,
  x1,
  y1,
  x2,
  y2,
  user_id
ORDER BY
  time ASC

panels.description: Gaussiana: esta visualización utiliza una distribución gaussiana (o normal) para representar los datos. Es una curva suave con forma de campana donde el pico representa el valor más común y el ancho de la "campana" muestra cuánta variación hay en los datos. Esto es útil para mostrar cuánto varía una métrica con respecto al promedio.

targets.rawSql:

date_trunc('$timeRange', timestamp_sensor) AS "time", 
  x1 as x1,
  x2 as x2,
  y1 as y1,
  y2 as y2, 
  uncertain
FROM
  etlocationuser
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(timestamp_sensor) AND user_id IN ($user_id)
GROUP BY
  time,
  x1,
  x2,
  y1,
  y2,
  uncertain
ORDER BY
  time

panels.description: muestren la actividad de los usuarios en función del tiempo o de otras variables relevantes. Esto te permitiría analizar el comportamiento de los usuarios en diferentes áreas. Puedes utilizar un gráfico de barras para visualizar la cantidad de registros de sensores por usuario, por hora del día o por área específica de la casa.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  date_trunc('$timeRange', timestamp_sensor) AS "time", 
  user_id,
  COUNT(*) AS activity
FROM
  etlocationuser
WHERE $__timeFilter(timestamp_sensor) AND user_id IN ($user_id)
GROUP BY
  time,
  user_id
ORDER BY
  time;
